---
title: Monitoring
description: Track account activity, audit user actions, analyze workflow and model performance, and monitor custom script execution in AI for Process.
---

The **Monitoring** module in AI for Process tracks events, actions, and changes across your account. Use it to maintain security, ensure compliance, and optimize performance across roles, integrations, models, workflows, users, datasets, guardrails, and the playground.

## Monitoring features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| [Audit Logs](./monitoring/audit-logs) | Time-stamped logs of all user actions and system events — from logins to model deployments. |
| [Workflow Analytics Dashboard](./monitoring/analytics/workflows-analytics-dashboard) | Real-time performance metrics for workflows deployed in your account. |
| [Model Analytics Dashboard](./monitoring/analytics/model-analytics-dashboard) | Performance tracking for deployed models. |
| [Model Traces](./monitoring/analytics/model-traces) | Run-level performance metrics and metadata for deployed models. |
| [Custom Scripts](./monitoring/monitoring-custom-scripts) | Run-level and log-level monitoring for custom scripts deployed in your account. |

## Best practices

- Regularly review audit logs, performance metrics, and model run analytics for security and compliance.
- Use filters to focus on specific events or users.
- Use time-based filters for targeted analysis.
